         <div>
            <head>14.5.1884 Mittwoch</head>
            <p>
               <placeName type="write" key="49069">Hamburg</placeName> May 14.
      Wednesday 1884.</p>
            <p>Bathed for the first time this year. The water was rather cold and I did
      not stop in very long. <persName key="1156">Robert</persName>
               <note type="reg">Blümer</note> is ill again. This is the
      third time and if it really is a &#x201e;rechute&#x201c; and not only a passing
      thing there is not much hope. Please God he may get well again. But I am afraid
      that even if he gets over again this attack he will die of a new rechute or of
      consumption later on, as the pain in the lungs never seems to get any better,
      and he has often complained to me of it. This time I believe the rechute was
      brought on by his going to <placeName key="49019">Rheinbeck</placeName> yesterday
      and coming back in the night air. It would be fearful if anything was to happen
      to him.</p>
         </div>
